<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1914-07-29T16:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1914-07-29T16:00:00-05:00" n="1548" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1548">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.51/73.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to Special Agent <persName type="to">Canova</persName>.</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1914-07-29T16:00:00-05:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">July 29, 1914—4
                                    p.m</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Department desires you proceed Zacatecas in accordance with its July
                                22, 3 p.m. You will avail yourself of every opportunity to <pb facs="0993" n="877" xml:id="pg_877"/> secure information as to
                                opinion of Constitutionalist leaders regarding the effect the decree
                                of July 14th of General Villareal against the church has
                                produced.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan</hi></signed>.</closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>